  "informal_statement": "For every real x ≥ 2, ∫_2^x (log t + 1)/(t² log² t) dt = 1/(2 log 2) − 1/(x log x).",
  "informal_proof_idea": "The integrand is the exact negative derivative of t ↦ 1/(t log t); verify the derivative pointwise and apply the fundamental theorem of calculus.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem mertens_weight_integral_closed_form :\n    ∀ x : ℝ, 2 ≤ x →\n      ∫ t in (2:ℝ)..x, (Real.log t + 1) / (t^2 * (Real.log t)^2)\n        = (2 * Real.log 2)⁻¹ - (x * Real.log x)⁻¹",
